While there is a lot of good content in this course, there is a disconnect with the videos and instructional info vs. the course download materials. I brought this to the attention of your support team and they just asked me to be the one to do more work by sending them examples of what I'm talking about when I already explained that things like a blank "Topic Wheel" template would great to include in the downloads. All you have to do is flag the course creator (Dennis Yu) or someone on his team to look into this. Since I'm specifically referencing something that is inherent to the course contents, that would be an appropriate course of action. Unfortunately, getting things resolved in these types of matters is painful and time intensive, so that reduces confidence on this Learn from Fiverr platform. You guys are competing with a whole host of learning platforms these days; many of which allow interaction directly with the instructor also. You should think of these things if you want stronger reviews and revenue.
